headline: Assessing Centene’s Value After 12% Stock Rebound and Medicaid Contract Expansion
summary: Trying to decide what to do with Centene's stock? You are not alone. With shares closing recently at $35.61 and a valuation score of 5 out of a possible 6, this healthcare insurer keeps investors guessing. The past month saw Centene gaining a robust 12.1%, a sharp turnaround after a tough stretch that included a year-to-date tumble of 41.2% and a staggering 57.4% three-year loss. Clearly, sentiment has shifted recently, but the big question is, why? Some of this volatility can be traced to...
